ass=m><span class=title> Re: rounding up bloodgills</span><hr size=1> I mix it up between running a zig-zag pattern or a big square around them.  If you're feeling your oats, some suggest running through the middle of your quad (skin up, obviously) but I have never tried that one. <p><BR><BR><img src=http://www.pcis.net/gurvy/gecko/sig2.jpg><BR><A HREF=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=79455 target=new>Player Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usarta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 9:34:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: rounding up bloodgills</span><hr size=1> Yeah, running through the middle of your quad will definitely help round them up.  I've had to do this (or done it inadvertently) quite a few times.  I've found that generally I can take a combat round or two of being pummeled by 4 mobs without problems -- even without a skin spell up.  But then again, I do stupid things like this.<br><br>However, with BG you should be able to round them up fairly well on the piece of shore you are pulling to, assuming you are pulling to the ruins on the shore of the lake (somewhere around -380, -1180).   Just get them to shore and if they aren't bunched well, begin running in circles around them.  When they look bunched in the F9 view, run back over the water to slow them down a bit, run them back to shore, snare, and begin CoF'ing them to death.  You may have to resnare -- they have 1300 hp, which would mean 7 CoF's assuming normal resists.<br><br>Sarta Intoxicaster,<br>Drunken Taxi of the 55th Level<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uminen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>minen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/4/02 12:27:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: rounding up bloodgills</span><hr size=1> Well, I am not a wizard, but as a Bard I always ran in circles to get my bloodgills bunched up.  Seemed to work very well.  One or 2 circles always got the so close it looked like on Bloodgill.<br><br>Minen<br>51 Bard<br>Vaz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugavoldalf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gavoldalf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/4/02 4:15:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: rounding up bloodgills</span><hr size=1> Thanks, I figured out running around them works quite well after having died 9 times running straight through the middle of em (stunned me and broke skin)<br>Thanks all, I leveled up 3 levels in 2 days on BG's<br><br>Gavoldalf Mhoramil &lt;Eternal Fury&gt;<br>Tribunal<br>Wizard of the fourty fourth tier <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=253.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=253.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><